    <h1 class="proj-header">About</h1>
    
    <p>There are <a href="https://www.globalgoals.org/goals/">17 Global Goals</a> that are set by the United Nations to promote and measure sustainable social, political, and economic development across the world.</p>
    <p>By using <a href="https://www.scb.se/hitta-statistik/statistik-efter-amne/miljo/miljoekonomi-och-hallbar-utveckling/indikatorer-for-hallbar-utveckling/pong/tabell-och-diagram/agenda-2030-lagesbild-2020--tabellbilagor2/">data</a> from <i>Statistics Sweden (SCB)</i>, this site explores whether Sweden has reached these goals and trends in recent years.</p>
    <p>The areas that will be the main focus of this study are two of the seventeen Global Goals - <i><a href="https://www.globalgoals.org/goals/4-quality-education/">Quality Education</a></i> and <i><a href="https://www.globalgoals.org/goals/10-reduced-inequalities/">Reduced Inequalities</a></i>.</p>

